24 ounce Yukon Gold Potatoes
4 clove Garlic
2 unit Blood Orange
28 ounce Sirloin Steak
½ ounce Chives
½ cup Parmesan Cheese
4 ounce Mixed Greens
3 teaspoon Vegetable Oil
4 tablespoon Butter
2 teaspoon Olive Oil
Salt
Pepper

Adjust rack to top position, then
preheat oven to 450 degrees. Lightly
oil a baking sheet. Wash and dry all
produce. Slice potatoes into ¼-inchthick rounds. Toss on prepared sheet
with a large drizzle of oil, salt, and
pepper. Bake until lightly browned and
tender, about 20 minutes.

Meanwhile, mince or grate garlic.
Peel blood oranges, then slice crosswise
into rounds. Thinly slice chives.

Pat steak dry with paper towels;
season all over with salt and pepper.
Heat a large drizzle of oil in a medium
pan over medium-high heat. Add steak
and cook to desired doneness, 4-7
minutes per side. Turn off heat. Remove
from pan and set aside to rest for 5
minutes. Wipe out pan.

Once potatoes have roasted 20
minutes, flip and evenly sprinkle with
Parmesan. Return to oven until cheese
is browned and melted, 5-10 minutes.

Heat 3 TBSP butter in same pan
over medium heat. Add garlic and cook
until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Reduce
heat to low, then stir in chives until
thoroughly combined. Turn off heat.
Season generously with salt and pepper.

In a medium bowl, combine orange
rounds, spring mix, a drizzle of olive oil,
salt, and pepper. Slice steak against the
grain. Divide salad, finished potatoes,
and steak between plates. Top steak
with sauce.